      • runSingleStep

        void runSingleStep()
            throws Exception,
                   epanet.core.EpanetException
        Execute a only step (iteration) of algorithm for call. It method is used by GUI because let cancel the execution.
        Throws:
        epanet.core.EpanetException - If there is a problem in the simulation of solution using EpanetToolkit
        Exception - If there is a problem in the close method of problem

      • isStoppingConditionReached

        boolean isStoppingConditionReached()
        Method to decide when the algorithm execution must stop. It would be called by run() and runSingleStep() to verify if the algorithm can continue his execution.
        Returns:
        a boolean that indicate if the algorithm execution can continue or not.

      • getStatusOfExecution

        @NotNull
@NotNull String getStatusOfExecution()
        Get a string with the status of execution.

        A example of a message can be:

        Number of evaluation: 100/1000


        Notes:
        The string returned for this method will be showed when the algorithm running in the GUI.
        Returns:
        a string with the status or empty string.

      • getResult

        @NotNull
@NotNull List<Result> getResult()
        Get the result of the algorithm execution. A singleobjective metaheuristics should return a list with only one solution. In case of multiobjective metaheuristics it should return a list with more than one solution. In the rare case that there is no solution a empty list has to be returned.
        Returns:
        the solution or solutions given as result of execution of algorithm or empty list.

      • getName

        @NotNull
@NotNull String getName()
        Get the name of algorithm.
        Returns:
        the name of algorithm or empty string.
